    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\n\nAdd All-to-All (A2A) as an alternative communication backend for Decode Context Parallel (DCP).\n\nThe existing DCP implementation uses **AllGather + ReduceScatter (AG+RS)**, which requires 3 NCCL calls per attention layer (AllGather Q, AllGather K metadata, ReduceScatter output). This PR adds an **All-to-All** backend that exchanges partial attention outputs and their LSE values across ranks, then combines them locally with a Triton kernel. This reduces NCCL calls from 3 to 2 per layer, lowering per-step communication overhead for long-context decode.\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\nvllm serve <model> --tp 16 --dcp 16 --dcp-comm-backend a2a\n```\n\nResolves: https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/34018\n\n**Key changes:**\n- `vllm/v1/attention/ops/dcp_alltoall.py` — New module: A2A communication + Triton LSE-weighted combine kernel\n- `vllm/config/parallel.py` — Add `--dcp-comm-backend` option (`ag_rs` | `a2a`) with validation\n- `vllm/v1/attention/backends/flash_attn.py` — Route decode output through A2A when configured\n- `vllm/v1/attention/backends/flashinfer.py` — Route decode output through A2A when configured\n- `vllm/model_executor/layers/attention/mla_attention.py` — Route MLA decode output through A2A when configured\n- `vllm/platforms/cuda.py` — Guard FlashInferMLA with DCP (no LSE support); force PIECEWISE for GQA+DCP\n- `vllm/distributed/parallel_state.py` — Add `get_kvp_group()` for A2A communication group\n- `tests/distributed/test_dcp_a2a.py` — Unit tests for config validation and LSE combine correctness\n\nReference: https://arxiv.org/abs/2507.07120\n\n## Test Plan\n\n1. **Unit tests (no GPU):**\n```bash\npython -m pytest tests/distributed/test_dcp_a2a.py -v\n```\n\n2. **Functional sanity check (8-GPU, DeepSeek-V2-Lite MLA):**\n```bash\n# Start server with A2A backend (DCP=4 example)\nvllm serve deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V2-Lite-Chat \\\n    --dtype bfloat16 --max-model-len 4096 --max-num-seqs 32 \\\n    --tensor-parallel-size 8 --decode-context-parallel-size 4 \\\n    --dcp-comm-backend a2a --enable-chunked-prefill --trust-remote-code\n\n# Verify correct output (not gibberish)\ncurl -s http://localhost:8000/v1/completions \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d '{\"model\":\"deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V2-Lite-Chat\",\"prompt\":\"What is 2+2? Answer with just the number:\",\"max_tokens\":10,\"temperature\":0}'\n```\n\nTested with DCP=2,4,8 for both A2A and AG+RS (default) backends. CUDA graph compatibility verified: A2A works with FULL CUDA graphs (MLA models).\n\n3. **CUDA graph compatibility verified:** A2A works with FULL CUDA graphs (MLA models) and PIECEWISE (GQA models).\n\n## Test Result\n\n**H200 8-GPU, DeepSeek-V2-Lite (MLA), FULL CUDA graphs:**\n\n| Suite | DCP=2 | DCP=4 | DCP=8 | Status |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------|--------|\n| AG+RS (baseline) | ✓ PASS | ✓ PASS | ✓ PASS | 3/3 |\n| A2A | ✓ PASS | ✓ PASS | ✓ PASS | 3/3 |\n\nAll tests produce correct output (verified against expected answers).\n\n**GB200 16-GPU, DeepSeek-V2-Lite (MLA), multi-node MNNVL:**\n\nTested with FlashInferMLA backend using [FlashInfer PR #2332](https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/pull/2332) (adds `return_lse` support for TRT-LLM MLA decode kernel). A2A correctness verified at DCP=2,4,8,16.\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
